  "texts": [
    "By comparing the distribution of ratings between LLMs and human raters and applying the Mann-Whitney U test, we identified any differences in how specific criteria are rated by each group.",
    "Lastly, RQ3 explores the factors influencing the reasoning processes behind the evaluations.",
    "In Section 4.5, we analyzed inter-category correlations for both human raters and LLMs.",
    "This analysis helps us understand which categories have the strongest associations with the overall score, providing insights into the reasoning processes of both humans and LLMs and identifying which criteria most significantly influence the holistic assessment.",
    "ResultsIn the following section, we explore the discrepancies between real-world teacher assessments and open-as well as closed-source LLM-generated evaluations of student texts, aiming to address our three key research questions."
